item.dc:creator: @CoderChris CoderChris
item.description:
@CoderChris wrote:

sk8rdude461:

From what I remember, the 377 cache (most 317 clients load that cache, and are modified to load higher off of that) only have flo.dat perhaps if you just add the flo2.dat to the same archive the flo.dat is it will work. Unless in the methods you added specify another directory.

this is my new error

item.dc:creator: @CoderChris CoderChris
item.description:
@CoderChris wrote:

[quote=“Sessy Pk3r, post:6, topic:541750”][quote author=CoderChris link=topic=660617.msg4416854#msg4416854 date=1396307087]
i already have a flo2.dat … i cant see flo2.dat in my cache
[/quote]
Maybe this is your problem? Your client should still be able to load the file even if it’s hidden. Perhaps you have it in the wrong directory. Make sure the repacking method matches with the directory of the data file you added.

theres no error

There has to be a bug or something that indicates you failed at implementing the tutorial or else you would not be here. Pack the cache with what you have and test it out.[/quote]
omg,… NO thats not my problem , and my repacking method is fine… you obviously never used packed cache if you told me to make sure my show hidden files folder is checked,

item.title: (317) Adding flo2.dat to Cache With Toms Cache Suite
item.dc:creator: @Sessy_Pk3r Sessy Pk3r
item.description:
@Sessy_Pk3r wrote:

CoderChris:

i already have a flo2.dat … i cant see flo2.dat in my cache

Maybe this is your problem? Your client should still be able to load the file even if it’s hidden. Perhaps you have it in the wrong directory. Make sure the repacking method matches with the directory of the data file you added.

CoderChris:

theres no error

There has to be a bug or something that indicates you failed at implementing the tutorial or else you would not be here. Pack the cache with what you have and test it out.
